        "gradings": [
          "Allamah Baqir al-Majlisi: <span> مرسل    </span> - Mir‘at al ‘Uqul Fi Sharh Akhbar Al al Rasul (20/48)"
        ],
        "index": 9450,
        "local_index": 1,
        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/al-kafi:5:3:25:1",
        "text": [
          "<span class=\"first-chapter-phrase\"><span class=\"first-in-chapter\">ع</span>ِدَّةٌ مِنْ أَصْحَابِنَا</span> عَنْ أَحْمَدَ بْنِ مُحَمَّدٍ عَنْ عَلِيِّ بْنِ الْحَكَمِ عَنْ أَبَانٍ عَنْ رَجُلٍ عَنْ أَبِي عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ( عليه السلام ) قَالَ الْكُفْوُ أَنْ يَكُونَ عَفِيفاً وَ عِنْدَهُ يَسَارٌ ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.hubeali": [
            "A number of our companions, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad, from Ali Bin Al hakam, from Aban, from a man, ",
            "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The match is that he happens to be chaste, and with him is wealth’."
          ],
          "en.sarwar": [
            "1. A number of our people have narrated from Ahmad ibn Muhammad from Ali ibn al-Hakam from Aban from a man who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘Proper match is one who is chaste and affluent.’” "
          ]
        }
      }
    ]
